    <stitle>DIAMONDLIFE&#8482; (BOSCH PIN SLIDE) DISC BRAKES For Vehicles Built After June 2, 2002 - DESCRIPTION -
        CALIPER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CALIPER</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404704">Figure 4</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="f0404704"/>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <para>The caliper (Item 1) is a single piece casting which contains an internal fluid passageway between the two
            hydraulic piston bores (Item 2). The piston bores contain the two pistons, piston boots (Items 3 and 4) and
            piston seals which are not visible.
        </para>
        <para>There are two different sizes of the pin slide disc brake assemblies: 66 mm and 73 mm. These calipers can
            be used in the following combinations based on specific vehicle applications:
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>66 mm front and rear</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>66 mm front and 73 mm rear</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>73 mm front and rear</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>The specific caliper combinations depends on the load rating for the vehicle.</para>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>NEVER change the caliper size in the field from what was original equipment on the vehicle.</para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
